<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,310,755,781]" box="[189,310,755,781]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,755,781]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,755,781]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[189,1399,801,933]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Large-sized 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Winnertz" authorityYear="1867" box="[332,438,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" genus="Bradysia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[332,438,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Bradysia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Brown. Maxillary palpus with 3 segments, segment 1 with a small shallow sensory patch. Wing length 
<quantity box="[414,506,837,863]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
, anal lobe small. Setose intercoxal lobe of hypopopygium present. Gonocoxa and gonostylus broad; gonocoxa with elongated ventromesial setae; gonostylus bulged mesiad, with a short apical tooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
